  "prompt": "When will IBM start pool receuitment drive for freshers of batch 2017?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, I cannot provide you with the exact dates or guarantee that IBM will have a pool recruitment drive for the 2017 batch. Recruitment plans depend on many factors, including IBM's hiring needs, budget, and the availability of suitable candidates.\n\nHowever, here's a general approach you can take to find potential opportunities with IBM for the 2017 batch:\n\n1.  **IBM Careers Website:**\n    *   Keep a close eye on the official IBM careers website:  [https://www.ibm.com/careers/](https://www.ibm.com/careers/) or look for a country-specific IBM career page (e.g., IBM India Careers).\n    *   Search for \"entry-level,\" \"graduate,\" \"associate,\" or \"fresh graduate\" positions.  Use keywords like \"2017 batch.\"\n    *   Set up job alerts for relevant roles.\n\n2.  **LinkedIn:**\n    *   Follow IBM's company page on LinkedIn.\n    *   Search for jobs at IBM using relevant keywords.\n    *   Connect with IBM recruiters and employees.  See if they have any information about upcoming hiring.\n\n3.  **Job Boards:**\n    *   Regularly check popular job boards like Naukri.com, Indeed, Glassdoor, and others relevant to your location.\n    *   Filter by entry-level positions and target IBM.\n\n4.  **University Placement Cells:**\n    *   If you are an alumnus of a university, stay in touch with the placement cell. They might receive information about IBM's recruitment drives or have connections with IBM recruiters.\n\n5.  **Recruitment Events and Job Fairs:**\n    *   Attend career fairs and recruitment events in your area or online.  IBM might have a presence at some of these events.\n\n6. **Networking:** Reach out to people who already work at IBM. Asking them about the company can help you determine if you want to work there.\n",
